### Upload the encrypted data bag items

* The `delivery-truck` cookbook's `publish` recipe takes care of uploading the `awesome_customers` cookbook to Chef server for us &ndash; all we needed to do was set the node attribute and include the `delivery-truck::publish` recipe from our build cookbook's `publish` recipe.
* We need to upload the data bags manually.
* Chef Delivery runs build cookbooks in local mode, which means that the cookbook runs with a temporary, in-memory Chef server (we introduced running `chef-client` in local mode [in the first tutorial](/learn-the-basics/rhel/make-your-recipe-more-manageable#step4). In order to upload the encrypted data bags to the Chef server, we need to change the behavior of `chef-client` to work with our Chef server.

To do that, you call the `with_server_config` helper method. This helper method sets the Chef server configuration, calls the provided block, and then restores the previous configuration.

* To upload the encrypted data bag items, we'll use the built-in `execute` resource to run the `knife` command.
* We need to both create the data bag and then upload our two data bag items (the database root password and the administrator password.)
* Explain why we need `--config` (see note below).
* We use a `not_if` guard to ensure that the data bag is created only when it doesn't exist.
* We upload the data bag items each time in case they ever change.

[PRODNOTE] Why do we need `--config` if we're already saying `with_server_config`? It seeme redundant, but it's the only way that works.

Write out your build cookbook's `publish` recipe like this.

```ruby
# ~/Development/deliver-customers-rhel/.delivery/build-cookbook/recipes/publish.rb
include_recipe 'delivery-truck::publish'

with_server_config do
  execute 'create passwords data bag' do
    cwd node['delivery']['workspace']['repo']
    command "knife data bag create passwords --config #{delivery_knife_rb}"
    not_if "knife data bag list --config #{delivery_knife_rb} | grep '^passwords$'"
  end
  %w(db_admin_password sql_server_root_password).each do |data_bag_item|
    execute "create #{data_bag_item} data bag item" do
      cwd node['delivery']['workspace']['repo']
      command "knife data bag from file passwords #{data_bag_item}.json --config #{delivery_knife_rb}"
    end
  end
end
```

